> Peter Piper plucked a plate of ponzu plum pork chops. At least, we bet he
> would have once he got a taste of tonight's dinner. It stars an indulgent,
> flavorful sauce made with ponzu, plum jam, and Sriracha—thickened just
> enough to coat juicy pork chops. You won't be mad if some of that
> tangy-sweet sauce drips onto the tender cauliflower rice and sesame roasted
> broccoli.

Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry
produce.

Cut @broccoli florets{8%ounce} into bite-size pieces if necessary. Trim and
thinly slice @scallions{2}, separating whites from greens. Peel and mince or
grate @ginger{1%thumb}.

== Sesame Roasted Broccoli ==

Toss broccoli on a #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of oil, @salt{}, and
@pepper{}. Roast on top rack until browned and tender, ~{15-20%minutes}.

Once broccoli is browned and tender, carefully toss with half the
@sesame dressing{1.5%ounce} (all for 4 servings).

== Cauliflower Rice ==

While broccoli roasts, place @riced cauliflower{6%ounce} in a medium
#microwave-safe bowl{} (use a large bowl for 4 servings). Cover bowl with
#plastic wrap{} and poke a few holes in wrap. Microwave until tender,
about ~{5%minutes}.

Meanwhile, in a #small bowl{}, stir together @ponzu sauce{12%milliliters},
@plum jam{1}, half the @garlic powder{1%teaspoon}, half the
@Sriracha{1%teaspoon} (use more or less to your taste), ½ TBSP
@cornstarch{1%tablespoon}, and ¼ cup @water{1/4%cup} (1/3 cup for 4) until no
lumps remain.

Once cauliflower rice is tender, heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{1%teaspoon} in
a large #pan{} over medium-high heat. Add scallion whites, ginger, and
remaining garlic powder; cook, stirring, until fragrant, ~{1%minute}.

Stir cauliflower rice into pan. Season with salt and pepper. Remove from heat;
cover to keep warm.

== Ponzu Sauce ==

Pat @chicken cutlets{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{}; prick all over with a
#fork{}. Season all over with salt and pepper, then coat in remaining
cornstarch.

> Swap in chicken for pork (no need to prick all over!); cook 3-5 minutes per
> side.

Heat a large drizzle of oil in second large pan over medium-high heat. Add
pork and cook until browned and cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes} per side.

> TIP: Press pork down with a spatula to ensure evening browning.

Turn off heat; transfer pork to a #cutting board{} to rest. Wipe out pan.

Return pan used for pork to medium heat. Add sauce and cook, stirring, until
thickened, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Stir in @butter{1%tablespoon} until melted. Season with salt and pepper.

> TIP: If sauce seems too thick, stir in a splash of water.

Transfer pork to pan with sauce; turn to coat.

== To Serve ==

Warm pan with cauliflower rice over medium-high heat if needed; stir in half
the scallion greens and @butter{1%tablespoon}.

Slice pork crosswise.

Divide broccoli, cauliflower rice, and pork between plates. Drizzle pork and
cauliflower rice with any remaining sauce and sprinkle with remaining
scallion greens. Serve.